description: When Alan Cope was eighteen, he joined the army and went off to fight in World War II. Like every American, he felt a patriotic fervor burning in him after Japan's attack on Pearl Harbor. But he had little idea what he was getting into by enlisting. This graphic memoir tells the story of his life during wartime, of his journey from his home on the west coast to basic training in Kentucky to leave in New York City, to the battlefields of France, to the terrors of the Bulge and General Patton's drive on Germany and Prague.

description:
A spellbinding story of five heroes pushed to their limits!

It's 17th-century Japan, a time and place of violent upheaval, wandering Ronin, and mysterious Geisha. Into this strange and dangerous world come Wolverine, Pyslocke, Punisher, Hulk and Deadpool. Five of Marvel's greatest heroes - as you've never seen them before. Each has been wronged by a powerful tyrant. Each has taken a solemn vow - of vengeance!

Collecting 5 RONIN #1-5.
name: TPB

description:
When the Avengers pull a mysterious, tattered soldier from the sea, they unwittingly bring back to life the Living Legend of World War II - a man whose memories of a life sixty years ago are as fresh as yesterday! How will Steve Rogers, frozen in suspended animation for half a century, adapt to the world of the 21st century? Brought to you by super-scribe Mark Waid (CAPTAIN AMERICA, AMAZING SPIDER-MAN) and AVENGERS: THE INITIATIVE artist Jorge Molina!

Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA: MAN OUT OF TIME #1-5, plus the classic AVENGERS #4 (1963).
name: HC/TPB

volume.name: Captain America: Man Out of Time

description: When Luke Skywalker, the New Republic's greatest hero and sole Jedi Master, decides to marry Mara Jade, the woman who was once the Emperor's personal assassin, you can be sure that hands both Imperial and New Republican will be raised to stop the marriage -- at any cost! Written by acclaimed Star Wars novelist Michael A. Stackpole (X-Wing Rogue Squadron; I, Jedi) and illustrated with photographic realism by Robert Teranishi, Union spotlights a monumental event in the Star Wars timeline that bridges the classic Star Wars trilogy to its boundless future a long time ago in a galaxy far, far away!
name: TPB

description: Born with the ability to look and sound like anyone, the shapeshifting Mystique is a former pro-mutant terrorist wanted by nearly every government in the world for alleged crimes against humanity. She's used her morphing powers to stand against the X-Men in their battle for mutant-human coexistence for years - but in this increasingly complicated world, Mystique begins to find the battle lines are no longer so clear. In exchange for protection from her countless enemies, Mystique reluctantly agrees to go to work for Professor Charles Xavier, telepathic leader of the X-Men. But instead of being invited to join the team, Mystique is asked to participate in politically sensitive operations as one of Xavier's secret agents, operatives who can't be traced back to Xavier in the event of their capture or death. Can this former mutant-rights terrorist, who can disguise herself as anyone on the planet, be trusted? Collecting MYSTIQUE #1-13.
name: TPB

description:
Witness the life and times of Ol' Shell-head - past, present and future and as seen through the eyes of his greatest foe! The Mandarin is a collection of lies, stories, myths and legends. But two things are true: He wears, upon each finger, an alien weapon of unimaginable power - and he's going to kill Tony Stark!

To defeat true evil, the Armored Avenger will have to soar to never before seen heights, and he's not going alone. Three generations of Starks face their ultimate foe, seventy-some years in the future - while in the present, Spider-Man joins Iron Man as he tries to fill in the blanks of his missing memory.

The future starts now for the Marvel Universe's favorite futurist.

Collecting IRON MAN ANNUAL #1 and INVINCIBLE IRON MAN #500.1 and #500, plus the story of Howard and Maria Stark's first meeting from INVINCIBLE IRON MAN #503!

description:
Frank Castle is back. Back for revenge. Back in New York. Back to cleaning its streets. Back together, healed and strong, his mission resumed as he partakes in the sweet wet work and notches up one of the highest body counts in Punisher history. Cyber sensei Henry Russo is back, keeping Frank proficient with an eye in the sky.

Others are back, as well - two of Frank's most sadistic enemies united in a new vindictive plot: Enter the Jigsaw Bothers!

Collecting PUNISHER: IN THE BLOOD #1-5.

description:
A proud legacy continues!

Eric Masterson was the first to wield the enchanted mace called Thunderstrike, and he sacrificed himself to save the world. But what happened to the mace? Has it been lost for all eternity, or does the world still need heroes? Has the time finally come for someone else to follow Eric's journey and take on the mantle of Thunderstrike?

Join us as the Marvel Universe welcomes back the everyman Avenger, Thunderstrike!

Collecting THUNDERSTRIKE #1-5 and material from THOR SPOTLIGHT.
name: TPB

description:
Captain America meets his ultimate nemesis: the Captain America of the Vietnam War!

As new enemies face off, old secrets from the Super-Soldier project are revealed. From the superstar WOLVERINE: WEAPON X creative team of Jason Aaron and Ron Garney, get ready for a hard-hitting story of one man's quest to serve his country - and the sacrifices he must make.

Collecting ULTIMATE COMICS CAPTAIN AMERICA #1-4 and material from CAPTAIN AMERICA SPOTLIGHT.

description:
Stardate 5440
The Enterprise has been ordered to deliver a pet waul to a Moauvian ambassador on the planet Waul.  The creature looks like a half bat, half cat but it is described by kirk as a cat/lizard animal.  As the waul is being moved to sickbay the cage breaks open and the waul gets out.  This causes problems for the crew as it is able to mentally project it's fear and aggression on the Enterprise crew who take on the it's personality.  This creates tensions between the Federation and Waul until M'Ress is able to calm the creature down as she is unaffected by the creature being a Caitian.
 
Special Note
This comic is odd in many aspects of the Enterprise Crew.  Nyota Uhura is a White with blonde hair and blue eyes.  Hikaru Sulu is a man of African decent, M'Ress no longer looks like a cat but has blue skin and green hair, and there is a Yeoman Conners who is also blonde but sounds like Pavel Chekov when you listen to the record.  
 
This is really odd in the cases of Uhura and Sulu as they look like the original actors who played the characters.  Another unique aspect to the coloring is the uniforms are different.  There are characters who are wearing blue who should be wearing red or gold.  The woman's legs are colored black as well as if they were wearing black leggings.
name: Passage To Moauv

description: The inaugural issue introduces Arion Nelkan during his final days as a soldier in the Athelican military machine, which is on a campaign of conquest against the handwaver nation of Ishtakar. Let’s just say that things don’t go exactly as planned…
name: Between Worlds (Part 1 of 6)

description: The epic showdown between a brother, a sister, and a handwaver hit squad – plus an unexpected revelation or two! (If we told you any more, we'd just spoil it.) Don't miss this action-packed (and extra-long) installment!
name: Between Worlds (Part 4 of 6)

description: Arion and Aliyana return to the Athelican capital, where their differences quickly set the siblings at odds. Meanwhile, their father (and Athelican Prime Minister) Kadin Nelkan meets with a mysterious handwaver woman, who has her own treacherous plans for the Nelkan family.
name: Between Worlds (Part 3 of 6)

description: Upon reaching the ancient fortress city of Adrost, Arion receives his long-awaited walking papers. But with them comes a peculiar invitation to a banquet from the even more peculiar Baron Lord Ardam – and there are one or two surprise guests in attendance as well.
name: Between Worlds (Part 2 of 6)

description: Tagged as a terrorist, Justin escapes his own unit and goes deep cover in search of answers. Meanwhile, psychological warfare succeeds with vulnerable Kaila, as she is sucked deeper into the clutches of a mysterious enemy who wants to exploit her power.

A secretive and high-powered conglomerate with unscrupulous ties, takes over security for the entire world. Believing they are responsible for a string of international murders and EMF bombings, and not knowing who to trust, Kaila infiltrates the dangerous organization on her own.

The journey to enlightenment is not an easy one. Past karma, conflicts, emotions and judgements cloud the path of three reluctant heroes as they battle their own inner demons while fighting evil in a black ops unit called the Deceivers. In this emotional issue, secrets are revealed and the hidden realm of the Draconian Warrior is unveiled as Kaila risks everything to help Justin understand the conflicts of his past. But his presence sparks an uprising not seen in Atlantis since its destruction thousands of years before. In the rage of battle, Kaila discovers deceit that rips into her very soul, beginning a catharsis that cuts her off from everyone she knows and loves. With the special recap book included, this becomes the perfect starting point for new readers!

When Lenny discovers a way to happiness through involvement in a new self-help movement called Scifiometry, Homer and his fellow barflies are determined to save their pal from financial and spiritual ruin.
name: Scam Wow!; Mousery

description: Redemption - can we forgive ourselves the deeds of our past? Haunting visions of the dead and undead plague Justin as memories of his battles flood back. Some very unexpected secrets are revealed when Kaila, out of empathy, tells him forbidden truths and leads him into the hidden realm of the Draconian Warriors. Atlantis plunges further into turmoil pitting our heroes against each other in a fight that could start a second war.

The action never lets up as Justin makes an ingenious escape from the bioterrorist he thinks killed his friend. Without a moment to breathe, Theros and Justin then must make a daring attempt to save Kaila from her captors. The team gets a chance to reunite only briefly as chaos threatens to destroy Atlantis and another high-ranking official disappears sparking yet another dangerous Deceiver mission.
 
General Notes
In issue #3 Rick Ketcham is mentioned to be inker in issue #2.
